### Test Inventory Service HTTP Endpoints

# Get all inventory (for reference)
GET http://localhost:3002/inventory/all

###

# Check single product stock (GET method)
GET http://localhost:3002/inventory/check-stock?productId=PROD001&quantity=5

###

# Check single product stock (POST method)  
POST http://localhost:3002/inventory/check-stock
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "PROD001",
  "quantity": 5
}

###

# Check multiple products stock
POST http://localhost:3002/inventory/check-multiple-stock
Content-Type: application/json

[
  {"productId": "PROD001", "quantity": 2},
  {"productId": "PROD002", "quantity": 3},
  {"productId": "PROD006", "quantity": 10}
]

###

# Test with out-of-stock product
GET http://localhost:3002/inventory/check-stock?productId=PROD007&quantity=1

###

# Test with non-existent product
GET http://localhost:3002/inventory/check-stock?productId=NONEXIST&quantity=1

